<plot>Guerrilla Guide to Politics (GGP) is a hip, high-energy, irreverent look at how young people can become involved in the democratic process. Instead of being preachy, it speaks to the audience with friendly banter, empowering them to exercise their civic muscles. The show breaks down complicated civics lessons into manageable segments, highlighting practical topics such as how to register, how to vote, and how to contact public officials. By using a cutting edge sound track, quick cuts, and high-powered graphics, Guerrilla Guide never loses its young audience.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?224131</url></doc>
